1
00:00:56,639 --> 00:00:59,684
In-guk, this is weird.

2
00:00:59,893 --> 00:01:01,853
I know this can't be,

3
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:04,314
but strangely, my body feels light.

4
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:07,734
I bet. It's because we overslept.

5
00:01:07,942 --> 00:01:09,444
I see.

6
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:12,614
-It's not the weekend, right?
-No.

7
00:01:12,822 --> 00:01:15,658
-It's not a national holiday, either.
-Right.

8
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:26,628
In-guk, didn't you hear the alarm?

9
00:01:26,711 --> 00:01:28,838
-Why didn't you wake up?
-Beats me.

10
00:01:29,088 --> 00:01:30,799
Why didn't you wake me up?

11
00:01:30,882 --> 00:01:32,842
You didn't on purpose
to be late for school, didn't you?

12
00:01:33,009 --> 00:01:34,344
I'm not sure.

13
00:01:36,304 --> 00:01:37,555
Come on.

14
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,602
Wake up. Please.

15
00:01:47,524 --> 00:01:48,650
-Hello.
-Hi.

16
00:01:49,317 --> 00:01:51,486
-Hello.
-Hello.

17
00:01:52,487 --> 00:01:53,530
Good morning.

18
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:55,532
Hello, sir.

19
00:02:31,985 --> 00:02:33,278
I'll clean up.

20
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:39,492
You need to get to work.

21
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:41,995
You didn't get much sleep, either.

22
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:44,873
Are you worried about me?

23
00:02:45,498 --> 00:02:46,583
I'm sorry.

24
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:49,502
I'll clean it up. I made the mess.

25
00:02:55,884 --> 00:02:56,843
-Hi, ma'am.
-Hello.

26
00:02:56,926 --> 00:02:57,927
Hello.

27
00:02:58,678 --> 00:02:59,721
-Hi.
-Hello.

28
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:01,389
Is Ms. Hwang here yet?

29
00:03:01,472 --> 00:03:02,390
Well...

30
00:03:02,473 --> 00:03:04,601
-Let's have a meeting this morning.
-Okay.

31
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:17,822
It's not even urgent.
Why did you stay all up night?

32
00:03:18,573 --> 00:03:19,574
What?

33
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:21,743
Just because.

34
00:03:23,912 --> 00:03:27,790
I have a lot of footages,
so I've been getting stressed.

35
00:03:27,999 --> 00:03:29,459
And I had a slight headache.

36
00:03:29,542 --> 00:03:31,210
You worked when you had a headache?

37
00:03:31,794 --> 00:03:33,755
That means you're a workaholic.

38
00:03:33,922 --> 00:03:36,174
It's better than being a gambler
or a drug addict.

39
00:03:36,382 --> 00:03:38,968
Most people would do
something called resting.

40
00:03:39,052 --> 00:03:41,721
I see. You're right.

41
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:07,121
You never go for a run.
Why did you suddenly want to run?

42
00:04:07,538 --> 00:04:08,915
You didn't get much sleep, either.

43
00:04:09,207 --> 00:04:11,834
You're right. Why won't you let me sleep?

44
00:04:12,752 --> 00:04:14,754
People might get the wrong idea.

45
00:04:15,421 --> 00:04:16,673
Aren't you tired?

46
00:04:17,632 --> 00:04:20,718
Something didn't feel right
when I was with them.

47
00:04:21,636 --> 00:04:22,679
Them?

48
00:04:47,996 --> 00:04:49,747
They seemed younger than I expected.

49
00:04:49,831 --> 00:04:51,791
Who? You?

50
00:04:51,874 --> 00:04:52,875
No, them.

51
00:04:53,001 --> 00:04:54,711
What's wrong with that? What?

52
00:04:54,794 --> 00:04:56,170
They were prettier than I remembered.

53
00:04:56,254 --> 00:04:58,798
What's your point? You're prettier.

54
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:00,174
Obviously.

55
00:05:00,466 --> 00:05:02,343
Then, what's wrong? What is it?

56
00:05:02,677 --> 00:05:03,928
I'm prettier,

57
00:05:04,637 --> 00:05:07,056
but it wasn't overwhelming.

58
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,725
Goodness, damn it.

59
00:05:12,186 --> 00:05:14,022
I'm an actress, so I take care of myself.

60
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:15,857
Even without that,
I was prettier than them.

61
00:05:15,940 --> 00:05:18,067
So I should be overwhelmingly
prettier than them.

62
00:05:18,693 --> 00:05:21,654
but for some reason,
my presence wasn't overwhelming.

63
00:05:21,738 --> 00:05:25,908
So you're saying that you won,
but you own by decision?

64
00:05:25,992 --> 00:05:27,910
You didn't knock them out.
You scored more points?

65
00:05:27,994 --> 00:05:29,996
Is that why something doesn't feel right?

66
00:05:30,955 --> 00:05:33,791
No, there shouldn't have been a match,
to begin with.

67
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:38,129
But I think you're setting up
the match on your own.

68
00:05:38,254 --> 00:05:39,672
Let's go. Get up.

69
00:05:39,797 --> 00:05:42,091
I won't go. Hey.

70
00:05:43,051 --> 00:05:45,678
You'll age faster
if you run without getting enough sleep.

71
00:05:47,013 --> 00:05:48,264
Stop running.

72
00:05:50,808 --> 00:05:51,851
I won't do it.

73
00:05:53,269 --> 00:05:54,312
I won't.

74
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:58,900
JU-YEON, SIN-AE, AND HO-PAL
LOOK AT HER AS IF THEY FIND HER PATHETIC

75
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:05,907
SHE AWKWARDLY WINS AT HO-PAL

76
00:06:16,084 --> 00:06:17,585
-Jin-joo.
-Yes?

77
00:06:17,668 --> 00:06:18,753
It's hard, isn't it?

78
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:21,923
No, I'm okay.
I just feel like I'm going to die soon.

79
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:24,801
You're okay. You didn't say
you were about to die right away.

80
00:06:25,843 --> 00:06:26,969
I'm happy.

81
00:06:31,599 --> 00:06:32,809
Rest for a bit.

82
00:06:33,059 --> 00:06:35,645
Yes. I think I need to rest.

83
00:06:36,270 --> 00:06:38,439
-How should I rest?
-While sitting up.

84
00:06:39,982 --> 00:06:41,275
While writing your script.

85
00:06:43,027 --> 00:06:45,071
Right. Rest up like that.

86
00:06:45,404 --> 00:06:48,199
You give me a lot of moral support.

87
00:06:48,616 --> 00:06:49,742
I'm glad to hear it.

88
00:06:55,957 --> 00:06:57,291
She's working hard on her scripts.

89
00:06:57,375 --> 00:06:59,836
How can I ask her to include
a massage chair in her scripts?

90
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:04,757
I'm happy to get sponsors, but still.

91
00:07:06,676 --> 00:07:08,302
Whatever. Anyway,
until she finishes the script

92
00:07:08,386 --> 00:07:09,929
for the eighth episode, don't call her.

93
00:07:10,012 --> 00:07:12,390
Besides, why massage chairs?
I won't accept that.

94
00:07:12,473 --> 00:07:13,724
Are we clear?

95
00:07:18,521 --> 00:07:21,232
-Hey, why are you so upset this morning?
-Your face is more upsetting.

96
00:07:21,357 --> 00:07:22,775
Are we running an inn here?

97
00:07:23,568 --> 00:07:25,528
He's busy
because he'll start filming soon.

98
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:28,823
And I'm busy because I'm dating.
We're busy for different reasons.

99
00:07:29,157 --> 00:07:30,116
Good for you.

100
00:07:30,199 --> 00:07:31,993
-I guess things are going well.
-Yes.

101
00:07:32,076 --> 00:07:35,955
Hey, Da-mi doesn't answer my calls
or texts when she goes out for drinks.

102
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:39,041
I was really upset, so I did
the same thing to her yesterday.

103
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:40,585
So that's going well.

104
00:07:40,668 --> 00:07:43,671
Yes. I didn't check my phone last night
and went drinking and had fun.

105
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,965
-Do you know what happened to me, then?
-What happened?

106
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:47,258
I got tired.

107
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:52,096
Oh, right.
Something more important happened.

108
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:55,057
-What is it?
-Da-mi didn't text or call me at all.

109
00:07:56,851 --> 00:07:58,227
She can see right through me.

110
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:00,521
Just go to sleep.

111
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:02,523
Go to sleep.

112
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:05,193
I should drink a cup of horse bean tea.

113
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:34,055
I sort of expected this would happen.

114
00:08:34,138 --> 00:08:36,766
But my feelings for her were strong enough
to make me risk it.

115
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:40,144
If I were to disregard my feelings
because things may be awkward between us,

116
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:43,105
I thought that
it would be a silly thing to do.

117
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:45,483
If you need an explanation
to help you understand,

118
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:47,527
I will do so.

119
00:08:47,985 --> 00:08:49,779
You don't need to explain this to me.

120
00:08:51,113 --> 00:08:52,365
Don't worry.

121
00:08:53,991 --> 00:08:55,117
Will you keep avoiding me?

122
00:08:56,077 --> 00:08:58,287
-I didn't avoid you.
-Is that really true?

123
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:03,167
-I just turned away from you.
-They sound about the same.

124
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:06,212
Okay. I cannot force anything.

125
00:09:08,256 --> 00:09:09,423
I understand.

126
00:09:23,187 --> 00:09:24,188
Sir.

127
00:09:25,481 --> 00:09:28,442
-Do you want to arm-wrestle with me?
-Arm-wrestle?

128
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:31,821
It's an unexpected turn of events.

129
00:09:31,904 --> 00:09:35,032
I want to beat you at something.

130
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:37,451
With my strength.

131
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:40,580
Do you think you can beat me?

132
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:43,082
Well,

133
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:46,085
I don't think it will be hard.

134
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:01,976
What is this match for?

135
00:10:02,059 --> 00:10:04,395
Money? Honor? Love?

136
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:09,066
All right. Whatever it may be,
don't be a sore loser.

137
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:10,443
Even if there's no return match,

138
00:10:10,526 --> 00:10:11,736
you can't call the other a coward.

139
00:10:12,069 --> 00:10:12,987
Even if your wrists break,

140
00:10:13,070 --> 00:10:14,488
you'll cover medical bills on your own.

141
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:16,407
All right. Get ready. Go.

142
00:10:41,599 --> 00:10:44,310
-Why are you staring at me like that?
-I'm working.

143
00:10:44,393 --> 00:10:46,062
Sitting there is part of your job?

144
00:10:46,145 --> 00:10:50,191
You're a writer.
You shouldn't go out drinking,

145
00:10:50,274 --> 00:10:52,234
especially not with the president
of an agency,

146
00:10:52,735 --> 00:10:54,028
especially not with men.

147
00:10:54,111 --> 00:10:57,323
Which one is the problem?
His job or his gender?

148
00:10:57,406 --> 00:10:58,616
He is the problem itself.

149
00:10:58,699 --> 00:11:01,077
Mr. Sung, are you jealous?

150
00:11:03,746 --> 00:11:05,414
I'm the CP of this drama.

151
00:11:06,165 --> 00:11:07,750
I have to protect my writer.

152
00:11:08,751 --> 00:11:11,420
I don't think a writer whose drama
is about to be filmed should drink.

153
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:13,798
I heard the writer, Park Hae-yeong,
doesn't even eat raw food

154
00:11:14,006 --> 00:11:15,174
to avoid getting food poisoned.

155
00:11:15,257 --> 00:11:17,343
That's the responsibility of a writer.

156
00:11:19,678 --> 00:11:22,473
Just by looking at you, I feel exhausted.

157
00:11:22,556 --> 00:11:24,350
That's a skill.

158
00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:28,521
-Hello.
-Hi.

159
00:11:32,066 --> 00:11:34,151
I made an appointment with Ms. Jung.

160
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:35,778
I see. Okay. You can go in.

161
00:11:36,654 --> 00:11:39,448
-Did you cure your hangover?
-Welcome. Come in.

162
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:45,121
What? Why are you here?

163
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:47,248
I'm the CP of this drama.

164
00:11:48,749 --> 00:11:50,126
Didn't you know that?

165
00:11:50,251 --> 00:11:51,544
Why are you here?

166
00:11:53,003 --> 00:11:54,880
What would you like to drink?

167
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:56,757
Anything cold will do.

168
00:11:59,677 --> 00:12:02,179
I came by to give her the profiles
of the actors in my agency.

169
00:12:02,263 --> 00:12:04,098
She said there were still
a few roles to fill.

170
00:12:04,890 --> 00:12:07,893
Did the president have to come himself?
It sounds more like a manager's job to me.

171
00:12:07,977 --> 00:12:09,437
No, I do things myself.

172
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:11,188
That way,
they'll get a chance to audition.

173
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:12,440
Give them to the director.

174
00:12:12,523 --> 00:12:15,401
Why did you barge into her studio?
You're distracting her from her job.

175
00:12:15,484 --> 00:12:17,194
She asked me to come, so I did.

176
00:12:17,361 --> 00:12:20,322
Considering the effort you make,
the outcome doesn't seem so great.

177
00:12:21,031 --> 00:12:22,825
That's why I work harder, sir.

178
00:12:22,908 --> 00:12:23,909
I said that to piss you off.

179
00:12:23,993 --> 00:12:25,619
-Why did you laugh?
-No, I'm pissed off.

180
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:27,496
That's how you look when you're pissed?

181
00:12:27,913 --> 00:12:30,374
Yes. This is how I look when I'm pissed.

182
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:36,172
You're ugly.

183
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:47,766
Please allow me to tell you
that you are twice...

184
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:51,353
No. You are three
to four times uglier than me.

185
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:56,942
Thank you for the cool drink.

186
00:12:57,401 --> 00:13:00,112
Here you go.
Here's the profile I promised you.

187
00:13:02,031 --> 00:13:04,241
I'll have a talk with the director.

188
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:05,784
Put in a good word for me.

189
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:08,078
-Which one of us is uglier?
-What?

190
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:12,374
Which one of us is uglier?

191
00:13:14,001 --> 00:13:15,628
What are you saying?

192
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:18,339
Mr. So is considered handsome.

193
00:13:18,422 --> 00:13:19,632
That's shocking.

194
00:13:20,841 --> 00:13:24,512
Then, are you telling me
that I'm considered ugly?

195
00:13:24,595 --> 00:13:26,180
That's shocking.

196
00:13:27,431 --> 00:13:30,476
Don't tell me that you didn't know
for the past 47 years.

197
00:13:32,269 --> 00:13:34,813
What on earth is going on here?

198
00:13:46,825 --> 00:13:48,661
I don't think
he really knew that about himself.

199
00:13:55,417 --> 00:13:56,710
What happened to your chin?

200
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:00,839
A shaving accident.

201
00:14:06,637 --> 00:14:08,097
Now that casting is done for the drama,

202
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:09,473
more PPL offers are coming in.

203
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:12,268
-That's great.
-Our director is the roadblock.

204
00:14:12,351 --> 00:14:14,728
He's famous for turning down
product placement.

205
00:14:14,812 --> 00:14:16,272
He is?

206
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:19,692
His reputation precedes him.
He said no to our marketing team.

207
00:14:26,949 --> 00:14:28,826
I see. The massage chair.

208
00:14:28,993 --> 00:14:31,620
The main character is a poor writer.

209
00:14:31,996 --> 00:14:33,789
It's hard to place this in the drama.

210
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:35,916
I know that you're crazy busy these days,

211
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,878
but you have eight years of experience
in marketing. Please handle this.

212
00:14:39,253 --> 00:14:41,839
There's too much money at stake
for me to side with the director.

213
00:14:42,089 --> 00:14:43,215
Okay.

214
00:14:46,135 --> 00:14:47,344
I'll do it.

215
00:14:49,221 --> 00:14:52,349
-What?
-Ms. Hwang has a lot of work these days.

216
00:14:52,474 --> 00:14:53,976
I can take care of something like this.

217
00:14:55,477 --> 00:14:57,688
I'm not trying to marginalize you,

218
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:01,150
but you've been in marketing
for eight weeks.

219
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:04,486
This isn't just something
you can casually take over.

220
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:09,617
It's important from whom I learned
the trade for eight weeks.

221
00:15:10,075 --> 00:15:11,160
I can do this.

222
00:15:15,664 --> 00:15:18,334
It stinks

223
00:15:23,672 --> 00:15:26,342
It's only natural

224
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:38,479
It's a nice song.

225
00:15:38,562 --> 00:15:40,981
Yes. This song is from Plan D Studio.

226
00:15:41,065 --> 00:15:43,734
The music director said
this might suit the drama well.

227
00:15:43,859 --> 00:15:47,321
I was informed that if you want it,
you can use it as a soundtrack.

228
00:15:47,571 --> 00:15:48,906
They are very eager to participate.

229
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:51,617
Should I set up a meeting?

230
00:15:54,745 --> 00:15:57,456
-Yes, please do.
-Okay, I will.

231
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,961
But what happened to your wrist?

232
00:16:03,003 --> 00:16:06,590
-Oh, this? I typed too much.
-I see.

233
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:10,094
-That must be hard.
-It's all right.

234
00:16:11,595 --> 00:16:12,972
I'm sorry to bring this up now,

235
00:16:13,055 --> 00:16:15,182
but this is the last of
product placement offers we received.

236
00:16:15,265 --> 00:16:16,392
FRIED CHICKEN

237
00:16:16,475 --> 00:16:19,770
MASSAGE CHAIRS
WE'LL SHOW YOU THE DIFFERENCE!

238
00:16:19,853 --> 00:16:22,731
Gosh. I know that it's hard realistically

239
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:25,693
to produce a drama without advertisement.
I've done this before, haven't I?

240
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:26,902
For my last drama,

241
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:29,113
I actually persuaded the writer
to include product placement.

242
00:16:29,363 --> 00:16:31,448
But a massage chair
doesn't fit in our drama.

243
00:16:31,532 --> 00:16:33,993
We have a small set to begin with.
Where would we put this?

244
00:16:34,326 --> 00:16:36,954
You can put it in for one episode
and take it out.

245
00:16:37,454 --> 00:16:40,040
This isn't a hand massager. It makes
no sense to take out a chair this big

246
00:16:40,124 --> 00:16:41,041
after using it for a day.

247
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:43,961
You can come up with an episode
that supports that.

248
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:47,464
The episode can be random.
You can just place it in one scene.

249
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:49,717
-It's easy.
-You think that's easy?

250
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:53,554
Of course, it is easy.
I can give you an example.

251
00:16:53,721 --> 00:16:56,724
-Mom.
-In-guk.

252
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:04,565
Mom. I've been worried.

253
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:08,902
My gosh. Tell me about it, my son.

254
00:17:09,069 --> 00:17:11,113
I am so bored.

255
00:17:11,321 --> 00:17:13,741
That's why you've been worried.

256
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:17,578
In that case,
let's spend our time in a meaningful way

257
00:17:17,661 --> 00:17:20,414
with something I prepared in advance.

258
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:29,923
Mom, what is this big thing?

259
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:33,761
You know what it is. Why ask?

260
00:17:33,844 --> 00:17:36,430
Mom, I don't really mind,
but I'm just curious.

261
00:17:36,513 --> 00:17:40,100
I told you I was bored,
but why are you on the massage chair?

262
00:17:40,934 --> 00:17:43,103
There's no context in this scene, anyway.

263
00:17:43,645 --> 00:17:46,940
Mom, I can't understand
what you just said.

264
00:17:47,107 --> 00:17:50,402
And why do we have a massage chair
all of a sudden?

265
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:52,946
I think that's kind of random.

266
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:56,450
In this world,
various types of lifestyles exist.

267
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:58,827
And at times, our beliefs
could be compromised based on

268
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:00,913
reasons we cannot say no to.

269
00:18:02,206 --> 00:18:05,751
It has to be placed in the drama
for 15 seconds. Please wait.

270
00:18:13,258 --> 00:18:14,635
Okay. It's good now.

271
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:17,805
I'll come down since it's been 15 seconds.

272
00:18:17,888 --> 00:18:21,809
Since you've started getting the massage,
you should finish it. I can wait.

273
00:18:21,892 --> 00:18:23,936
Shall I?

274
00:18:31,068 --> 00:18:33,862
-Like that?
-Yes, just like that.

275
00:18:36,073 --> 00:18:39,076
-You're a genius.
-Thank you.

276
00:18:40,494 --> 00:18:42,454
All right. Let's go talk this over
with my team.

277
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:45,666
Wait. Then, you'll include this
in your scene, right?

278
00:18:45,749 --> 00:18:46,959
We just did.

279
00:18:47,459 --> 00:18:48,836
We already did that.

280
00:18:52,089 --> 00:18:54,341
-Thank you. Good work.
-Gosh.

281
00:18:54,424 --> 00:18:55,467
It was nothing.

282
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:58,679
Since you worked hard,
you should have a sip of this.

283
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:00,389
Shall I?

284
00:19:16,196 --> 00:19:17,573
We're amazing.

285
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:20,075
-It's all good now. Let's go.
-Okay.

286
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:21,201
Let's go.

287
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:26,623
What should we get?

288
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:29,960
-This place serves good kimchi stew.
-Right.

289
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:31,879
We'd like to order, please.

290
00:19:38,677 --> 00:19:41,805
Excuse me. Weren't you on TV?

291
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:43,974
Yes.

292
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:46,435
I was on TV once. You recognized me.

293
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:50,439
I'm sorry, but could you please leave?

294
00:19:52,107 --> 00:19:53,817
I don't mind,

295
00:19:54,151 --> 00:19:57,237
but the owner asked you to leave.

296
00:20:04,828 --> 00:20:05,829
Okay.

297
00:20:07,748 --> 00:20:08,790
Let's go.

298
00:20:21,428 --> 00:20:22,471
Are you upset?

299
00:20:22,930 --> 00:20:25,515
Of course. We lost a restaurant
that serves good food.

300
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:27,726
Is their food good?

301
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:29,519
Yes.

302
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:31,063
That's a shame.

303
00:20:33,649 --> 00:20:34,942
Do you want pho?

304
00:20:35,817 --> 00:20:36,860
Sure.

305
00:20:57,923 --> 00:20:59,216
Lately,

306
00:21:00,092 --> 00:21:01,885
he's been showing up in my dreams a lot.

307
00:21:03,011 --> 00:21:05,222
Usually, he doesn't say anything

308
00:21:06,139 --> 00:21:08,058
or gets extremely mad at me.

309
00:21:09,142 --> 00:21:10,310
That's him in my dreams.

310
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:14,022
Have you seen him behave similarly before?

311
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:15,983
Not at all.

312
00:21:16,692 --> 00:21:18,193
He's not that kind of person.

313
00:21:19,653 --> 00:21:21,196
He always smiled

314
00:21:22,281 --> 00:21:23,657
and cheered me on.

315
00:21:25,784 --> 00:21:28,996
He was really committed to the point
that it could be boring.

316
00:21:29,788 --> 00:21:31,498
Are you worried
that he might be disappointed?

317
00:21:31,957 --> 00:21:33,875
-Pardon?
-What I mean is,

318
00:21:34,167 --> 00:21:37,004
are you worried it might seem
like you're trying to get over him

319
00:21:37,504 --> 00:21:40,590
and it would disappoint him?

320
00:21:41,591 --> 00:21:42,634
No.

321
00:21:48,015 --> 00:21:50,934
I feel like I'm using him.

322
00:21:55,230 --> 00:21:56,898
It's not that I'm disappointed.

323
00:21:58,900 --> 00:22:00,068
I feel sorry.

324
00:22:03,113 --> 00:22:04,281
I still

325
00:22:05,407 --> 00:22:07,284
need him.

326
00:22:11,121 --> 00:22:13,123
And I miss him.

327
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,626
So is that why

328
00:22:17,753 --> 00:22:19,087
I'm mad at myself?

329
00:22:21,631 --> 00:22:24,134
-I'm sorry.
-You can cry here.

330
00:22:39,983 --> 00:22:41,151
It's odd though.

331
00:22:41,276 --> 00:22:44,279
It's not your fault.
Why would you feel sorry?

332
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,698
Aren't you being too considerate?

333
00:22:46,782 --> 00:22:48,283
That might offend him more.

334
00:22:49,159 --> 00:22:50,368
If he does that again next time,

335
00:22:50,452 --> 00:22:52,829
don't lose to him.
Get angrier and yell at him.

336
00:22:53,330 --> 00:22:54,956
Have you two never fought?

337
00:22:55,332 --> 00:22:57,667
We never fought.

338
00:22:59,044 --> 00:23:00,712
You can take this opportunity, then.

339
00:23:00,796 --> 00:23:02,672
Have a big fight. Okay?

340
00:23:02,756 --> 00:23:05,342
He was the one who messed up.
Why is he making you the bad one?

341
00:23:05,801 --> 00:23:07,636
That's how all men are.

342
00:23:08,845 --> 00:23:10,263
Right.

343
00:23:11,014 --> 00:23:14,392
I'll give you an important mission.

344
00:23:15,060 --> 00:23:16,686
-A mission?
-Yes.

345
00:23:16,978 --> 00:23:19,314
-You must complete it, okay?
-Okay.

346
00:23:20,190 --> 00:23:21,650
Take a break from work.

347
00:23:21,733 --> 00:23:22,984
Well, that's...

348
00:23:23,068 --> 00:23:25,654
Don't people say that to you sometimes?

349
00:23:25,737 --> 00:23:26,905
"Why don't you go on a trip?"

350
00:23:27,030 --> 00:23:28,323
They all say that for a reason.

351
00:23:29,658 --> 00:23:31,743
Even if you don't call it a trip,

352
00:23:31,993 --> 00:23:34,287
spend some time
in a different environment.

353
00:23:35,622 --> 00:23:37,040
In a different environment?

354
00:23:38,375 --> 00:23:41,086
-You said that you made donations.
-Yes.

355
00:23:41,378 --> 00:23:43,046
Have you been to the charity organization?

356
00:23:43,630 --> 00:23:44,631
No.

357
00:23:45,048 --> 00:23:46,925
I just made donations to the foundation.

358
00:23:47,134 --> 00:23:48,635
That's easier, then.

359
00:23:49,219 --> 00:23:52,722
Treat it as a break and pay a visit.
I'm sure it will be helpful.

360
00:23:53,807 --> 00:23:56,768
They say that true rest is not at home.

361
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:32,846
What brings you here?

362
00:24:33,847 --> 00:24:35,223
Glad to see you didn't cook this time.

363
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:36,766
I'm hungry.

364
00:24:38,226 --> 00:24:40,687
You've never come here
because you were hungry.

365
00:24:41,438 --> 00:24:45,025
Well, I was walking and thought about us.

366
00:24:45,442 --> 00:24:47,777
When I did,
we looked like two pitiful siblings.

367
00:24:47,861 --> 00:24:49,279
You're hungry because we're pitiful?

368
00:24:50,322 --> 00:24:52,240
We need to have a lot of energy
to stay pitiful.

369
00:24:52,991 --> 00:24:54,284
You do have a point.

370
00:24:55,243 --> 00:24:57,287
I want to have a meal with my brother.

371
00:24:57,787 --> 00:24:59,122
I'll accept it.

372
00:25:02,626 --> 00:25:04,419
-Did something happen?
-Yes.

373
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:07,047
I had pho for lunch.

374
00:25:08,465 --> 00:25:10,091
I see.

375
00:25:11,009 --> 00:25:13,053
-Let's get Vietnamese spring rolls.
-Okay.

376
00:25:17,474 --> 00:25:19,851
I'm tired. Give me a piggyback ride.

377
00:25:20,477 --> 00:25:22,354
-Get on my back.
-Really?

378
00:25:22,479 --> 00:25:24,231
Is there a baby carrier around here?

379
00:25:24,314 --> 00:25:25,357
Really?

380
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:30,070
I'm tired.

381
00:25:47,671 --> 00:25:48,880
What's happening?

382
00:25:50,507 --> 00:25:51,549
This is sad.

383
00:25:54,261 --> 00:25:56,846
Are you crying
as you're writing your own script?

384
00:25:58,723 --> 00:26:00,850
Don't you laugh, cry, and say the lines

385
00:26:01,101 --> 00:26:02,143
when you write scripts?

386
00:26:02,227 --> 00:26:03,895
-I do.
-That's it.

387
00:26:03,979 --> 00:26:05,105
Goodness.

388
00:26:05,355 --> 00:26:07,482
Living my life is already hard enough.

389
00:26:07,941 --> 00:26:10,151
But a screenwriter has to keep up
with the characters' emotions.

390
00:26:10,235 --> 00:26:12,279
If so, shouldn't the screenwriter
work for half the time

391
00:26:12,362 --> 00:26:14,281
other people work for?

392
00:26:14,364 --> 00:26:15,365
That's a great line.

393
00:26:15,448 --> 00:26:16,950
I should use that.

394
00:26:17,409 --> 00:26:18,910
I know we work out of passion,

395
00:26:19,327 --> 00:26:21,997
but people have to understand
when screenwriters throw a fit.

396
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:24,207
I like that. Thanks.

397
00:26:28,295 --> 00:26:30,964
"You have to understand
when screenwriters throw a fit."

398
00:26:31,131 --> 00:26:32,173
Thanks.

399
00:26:34,217 --> 00:26:35,343
I'm tired.

400
00:26:44,060 --> 00:26:45,478
SMART SHAVER

401
00:26:58,283 --> 00:27:00,785
POMEGRANATE STICK WITH RED GINSENG

402
00:27:13,381 --> 00:27:15,300
Ms. Hwang, you must be tired.

403
00:27:15,383 --> 00:27:16,593
Make sure you take one.

404
00:27:23,266 --> 00:27:24,934
I don't get it.

405
00:27:27,062 --> 00:27:28,605
Is it because of my laugh lines?

406
00:27:38,448 --> 00:27:40,950
DERMATOLOGY CLINIC FOR LAUGH LINES

407
00:28:07,102 --> 00:28:08,478
Do you want to arm-wrestle?

408
00:28:12,273 --> 00:28:15,193
I lost my wrist.

409
00:28:26,329 --> 00:28:28,581
Let's play just one round. Just one round.
I'm serious.

410
00:28:28,748 --> 00:28:31,126
Give me your arm. Give it to me.

411
00:28:53,231 --> 00:28:56,151
Is this our first time having this dish?

412
00:28:58,695 --> 00:28:59,696
Yes.

413
00:29:09,581 --> 00:29:11,458
Can you give us one bowl of pho?

414
00:29:29,267 --> 00:29:30,602
Who bought you that?

415
00:29:33,563 --> 00:29:34,522
I bought it.

416
00:29:34,606 --> 00:29:36,775
You don't use electric shavers
because your beard is soft.

417
00:30:10,683 --> 00:30:11,684
YOU HAVE A NEW MESSAGE

418
00:30:12,519 --> 00:30:15,855
This is Ha-yun, Jae-hun's girlfriend.

419
00:30:16,064 --> 00:30:18,566
I can take care of my own boyfriend.

420
00:30:39,546 --> 00:30:42,549
THIS IS HA-YUN, JAE-HUN'S GIRLFRIEND
I CAN TAKE CARE OF MY OWN BOYFRIEND

421
00:30:50,682 --> 00:30:51,891
Damn it.

422
00:31:08,366 --> 00:31:09,868
You'll die if you keep running!

423
00:31:13,204 --> 00:31:16,332
I want to be happy even if I'm exhausted.

424
00:31:23,464 --> 00:31:24,674
You must be tired.

425
00:31:26,634 --> 00:31:28,219
At least, I sleep well.

426
00:31:30,263 --> 00:31:32,181
Preparing to shoot must be exhausting.

427
00:31:32,891 --> 00:31:34,517
I never took a break.

428
00:31:35,852 --> 00:31:38,187
It's hard to hire the staff, isn't it?

429
00:31:38,354 --> 00:31:41,190
The budget is the same, but the living
expenses and rates keep going up.

430
00:31:41,399 --> 00:31:43,568
We have never had enough budget,
to begin with.

431
00:31:44,777 --> 00:31:46,738
Isn't it tiring to be so handsome?

432
00:31:53,244 --> 00:31:56,164
I was making a joke
because everyone seemed exhausted.

433
00:31:56,247 --> 00:31:58,750
When I saw his face after making
that joke, I realized he's handsome,

434
00:31:58,833 --> 00:32:00,168
so the joke's on me.

435
00:32:09,344 --> 00:32:11,429
Drink this since you're tired.

436
00:32:12,180 --> 00:32:13,556
A light drink.

437
00:32:15,725 --> 00:32:17,101
That's enough.

438
00:32:40,917 --> 00:32:43,544
Let's do something fun.

439
00:32:45,421 --> 00:32:49,175
I can't work like this. Let's go somewhere
and have fun. We should stop working.

440
00:32:49,509 --> 00:32:52,261
I'm torn in two
because my heart wants to say yes,

441
00:32:52,345 --> 00:32:55,098
but my body knows I should say no.

442
00:32:55,181 --> 00:32:57,725
Will you follow your heart or your body?

443
00:33:02,230 --> 00:33:03,189
There's this saying.

444
00:33:03,272 --> 00:33:05,900
"One finds what one wants to find
when one's back from the trip to find it."

445
00:33:06,442 --> 00:33:07,819
We should go somewhere.

446
00:33:09,237 --> 00:33:12,156
Let's not get stressed out thinking
we should've picked a farther destination.

447
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,784
Let us be bold and go somewhere far.

448
00:33:15,201 --> 00:33:17,620
-Yes!
-Nice!

449
00:33:18,204 --> 00:33:19,414
Awesome!

450
00:33:19,497 --> 00:33:24,544
YEOSAN CITY HALL TO YEOSAN CATHEDRAL

451
00:33:24,627 --> 00:33:25,753
JANGEUNG CHURCH

452
00:33:26,045 --> 00:33:28,339
YEOSAN CITY HALL

453
00:33:28,423 --> 00:33:30,425
YEOSAN CATHEDRAL

454
00:34:13,718 --> 00:34:14,761
Hello.

455
00:34:17,638 --> 00:34:18,639
Welcome.

456
00:34:20,808 --> 00:34:23,311
As you requested,
I didn't tell them in advance.

457
00:34:23,394 --> 00:34:27,023
When they hear a sponsor is visiting,
they usually all come out and say hello.

458
00:34:27,398 --> 00:34:28,691
No, I don't want that.

459
00:34:28,983 --> 00:34:32,278
That's what I thought.
You can take your time to look around.

460
00:34:32,361 --> 00:34:34,489
You can talk to the kids later.

461
00:34:34,572 --> 00:34:37,617
Since you're here,
if you're up for any volunteer work,

462
00:34:37,700 --> 00:34:41,245
we have more than enough to give you.
You can get as much work as you want.

463
00:34:41,329 --> 00:34:42,914
We must give back as much as we received.

464
00:34:46,334 --> 00:34:47,794
Did that sound weird?

465
00:34:48,086 --> 00:34:50,546
I was joking. I'm sorry.

466
00:34:50,713 --> 00:34:52,924
-No, it was funny.
-Right?

467
00:34:54,467 --> 00:34:56,886
Do you want to take a photo
with the kids later?

468
00:34:58,137 --> 00:34:59,055
Is it not allowed?

469
00:34:59,138 --> 00:35:02,934
No, it's not that.
Our kids are used to taking group photos.

470
00:35:03,142 --> 00:35:06,562
It's just that we also look after
disabled kids here.

471
00:35:06,813 --> 00:35:09,107
A while ago, an assemblywoman came here.

472
00:35:09,649 --> 00:35:13,653
She insisted on giving a bath
to one of the kids. Damn her.

473
00:35:13,736 --> 00:35:16,614
She took a photo of that
and posted it on her social media,

474
00:35:16,697 --> 00:35:18,658
which made its way on the news, too.

475
00:35:21,577 --> 00:35:25,123
Although we know it wasn't intentional,
we tend to stay away from taking photos.

476
00:35:25,706 --> 00:35:26,666
I won't take any photos.

477
00:35:26,749 --> 00:35:30,169
No, you can take photos.
Just be careful when you do.

478
00:35:30,670 --> 00:35:32,922
-Okay.
-Okay. Shall we go in?

479
00:35:45,685 --> 00:35:47,520
-Aren't they beautiful?
-Yes.

480
00:35:47,603 --> 00:35:48,521
Goodness.

481
00:35:49,981 --> 00:35:51,482
-Stop it.
-Did you guys eat?

482
00:35:51,566 --> 00:35:53,484
-Yes.
-Okay. Don't go far.

483
00:35:53,568 --> 00:35:54,735
-Okay.
-Okay.

484
00:35:56,737 --> 00:35:58,030
-This is the cafeteria.
-Hey!

485
00:36:07,999 --> 00:36:09,458
You're eating raccoons.

486
00:36:11,169 --> 00:36:12,170
-Go away.
-Hey.

487
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:15,173
What's wrong? Are you leaving?

488
00:36:16,841 --> 00:36:19,468
No. That guy in there...

489
00:36:20,511 --> 00:36:22,680
-Do you know him?
-Is he doing some kind of

490
00:36:22,763 --> 00:36:25,057
community service here
to make up his crimes?

491
00:36:25,892 --> 00:36:27,894
Don't let him scare you.
He's not a criminal.

492
00:36:27,977 --> 00:36:31,063
He's our angelic donor. He's Chairman Kim.

493
00:36:31,147 --> 00:36:33,065
-Angelic?
-Yes.

494
00:36:33,149 --> 00:36:35,776
We call him the Chairman.

495
00:36:35,860 --> 00:36:38,404
Whenever he makes money,
he always makes a donation.

496
00:36:38,487 --> 00:36:40,531
I wondered
how he was going to feed himself.

497
00:36:40,740 --> 00:36:41,866
He comes here and eats.

498
00:36:42,158 --> 00:36:44,493
When he's not on a project,
he practically lives here.

499
00:37:01,802 --> 00:37:03,471
"Let's not get stressed out,

500
00:37:03,554 --> 00:37:05,806
thinking we should've picked
a farther destination."

501
00:37:06,349 --> 00:37:09,018
We were bold and came pretty far.
We're at Wolmido Island.

502
00:37:09,936 --> 00:37:11,395
Wolmido is far enough.

503
00:37:12,021 --> 00:37:14,398
There are over 20 subway stations
in between.

504
00:37:14,565 --> 00:37:16,567
I like it. There's the ocean, too.

505
00:37:17,318 --> 00:37:19,362
I like everything here.
The entertainment, food,

506
00:37:19,445 --> 00:37:21,447
and the sights. I like it.

507
00:37:22,490 --> 00:37:24,033
But we're here to work.

508
00:37:24,867 --> 00:37:26,118
What do you mean?

509
00:37:28,037 --> 00:37:30,039
Why did you choose a place in my script?

510
00:37:32,667 --> 00:37:34,669
You came here to check out the location
for your shoot.

511
00:37:34,961 --> 00:37:36,462
